ic system, and be able to design and determine the characteristics and performance of measurement and control functions.</p><p>Understanding of the dynamic behaviour of process systems and the effect of disturb</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Individual Student Control Engineering Computer Based ROGO Multiple Choice In Class Tests</li></ul><p>Process Safety</p><p>A2.6.0.1 Understand the inherent nature of safety and loss prevention, and the principal hazard sources in chemical and related processes – including flammability, explosivity and toxicity (including biological hazards).</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Group Design Project and in an individual student class test: Students to carry out HAZID/ HAZOP in the project</li></ul><p>A2.6.02 Understand the principles of risk assessment and of safety management, and be able to apply techniques for the assessment and abatement of process and product hazards.</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Group Design Project</li></ul><p>A2.6.0.3 Understand methods of identifying process hazards (e.g. HAZOP), and of assessing environmental impact.</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Group Design Project and by an in class test: Students to carry out HAZID/ HAZOP in the project</li></ul><p>Sustainability and Economics, Ethics</p><p>A2.7.0.3 Be able to apply the principles of process, plant and project economics.</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Group Design Project: Students to carry out CAPEX and OPEX estimations</li></ul><p>A4 – Chemical Engineering Design Practice &amp; Design Projects</p><p>A4.2.3 Be able to deploy chemical engineering knowledge using rigorous calculation and results analysis to arrive at and verify the realism of the chosen design</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Group Design Project</li></ul><p>A5 - Embedded Learning</p><p>A5.2.1 Have developed a wide range of problem-solving skills</p><ul> <li>Assessed in the Group Design Project</li></ul><p>A5.2.3 Recognise the importance of working effectively with others and have acquired a range of experience in achieving this.</p><p><span style="font-family:verdana,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;">Assessed in the Group Design Project through WebPA</span></span></p></div>',
